# Verification Before Success

**Assume you are NOT done until you can prove your solution works.** Use every single tool at your disposal. Do not declare success until you have verified in both compile time and runtime.

## Every Single Tool — Use Them

You must actively use every single tool to verify. Do not limit yourself. Use every single tool that applies.

### Native Cursor Tools

- **Shell** — run `bun run build`, verification scripts, any CLI command
- **Grep** — search codebase for patterns, verify usage
- **Read** — read files to confirm changes, check config
- **Write** / **StrReplace** — make fixes; then verify with Shell
- **Glob** — find relevant files (scripts, tests, config)
- **Delete** — remove obsolete files; verify build still works
- **ReadLints** — check changed files for lint errors
- **WebSearch** — look up docs, errors, version compatibility
- **mcp_web_fetch** — fetch URLs, API docs, external resources
- **TodoWrite** — track verification steps; mark complete only after proof
- **mcp_task** — launch subagents (explore, shell, docs-researcher, generalPurpose) to verify
- **call_mcp_tool** — call MCP tools directly
- **fetch_mcp_resource** — fetch MCP resources
- **GenerateImage** — when verifying UI/design changes
- **EditNotebook** — when verifying notebook-based workflows

