Apply `.cursor/rules/` — firestore-error-handling, use-bun-instead-of-node-vite-npm-pnpm, and this rule.

## Mandatory Verification

1. **Compile time**: Run `bun run build`. It must complete without errors. Do not assume — run the build again after changes.
2. **Runtime**: For UI, API, or user-facing changes, verify in the browser (or via MCP/scripts). The feature must work.

## Never Do

- Declare "I have successfully implemented..." without running build and (where applicable) runtime verification
- Assume a fix worked without re-running the build or re-testing
- Use only one tool when every single tool is available
- Skip any tool — use every single tool that could verify (MCP, scripts, browser, etc.)

## Always Do

- Run `bun run build` after making changes.
- Use every single tool when they apply — build + MCP + script + browser + all others.
- If build or runtime fails, fix it. Do not hand off unverified work.
